works.description: There is an elite group of individuals who are willing to spend a lot on the rarest and oldest of whiskies. For these whisky lovers, Glenmorangie distillery in the Scottish Highlands has announce new limited release, the Pride 1981, which is its most rare and luxurious single malt offering to date. The exceptional whisky was matured in the finest oak casks for 18 years before being aged exclusively in Chateau d’Yquem Sauternes casks for another 10 years (28 years, 9 months and 11 days in total).
